Wash and dry produce.

In a #small pot{}, bring @Israeli Couscous{5%ounce}, @Veggie Stock Concentrate{3}, and 1 1/2 cups water (3 cups for 4) to a boil. Once boiling, cover and reduce to a low simmer.

> Start with hot water to help the water boil faster.

Cook until tender, ~{6-8%minutes}. Keep covered until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, halve @Falafel{10}.

Drizzle @Cooking Oil{1%tsp} in a hot pan. Cook falafel until golden and crispy, ~{2-3%minutes} per side.

While falafel cooks, in a #bowl{}, mix @Smoky Garlic Herb Sauce{1%ounce} and @Sour Cream{1.5%tablespoon}.

Dice @Mini Cucumber{1}(diced). Halve @Grape Tomatoes{4%ounce}(halved). Roughly chop @Dill{1/4%ounce}(roughly chopped). Quarter @Lemon{1}(quartered).

In a separate bowl, mix cucumber, tomatoes, dill, @Feta Cheese{1/2%cup}, 1 TBSP @Olive Oil{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4), and juice from half the lemon. Taste and season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}.

Toast @Pita Bread{2}; spread with half the @Garlic Herb Butter{2%tablespoon}. Cut into quarters.

Fluff couscous; stir in @Pistachios{1/2%ounce} and remaining garlic herb butter.

Divide couscous between plates; serve with falafel, pitas, cucumber salad, and remaining lemon wedges. Drizzle falafel with garlic herb crema and as much @Hot Sauce{2%teaspoon} as you like.